 The accident, undoubtedly, left an expecting Macci D patron with an empty stomach after a prang that most likely converted the order of slap-chips to mash. The accident took place on the corner of Walter Sisulu- and Dr Beyers Naude Drive on Sunday morning around 10:00 after the delivery vehicle and a taxi collided. The McDonald’s Head Office was contacted for comment and informed that fortunately, no injuries were sustained. It remains unknown what the cause of the accident was or whether the unhappy patron, ever got his happy meal.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za